description: TEHRAN- The director general of the Consular Department at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs has highlighted the ongoing efforts to secure the release of two Iranian pilgrims from Saudi Arabian prisons.
title: Diplomatic efforts underway to release Iranian pilgrims held in Saudi Arabia

description: TEHRAN - The spokesman of the Guardian Council announced the election of the council's presiding board and the retention of the previous members in their positions.
title: Jannati re-elected as secretary of Iran's Guardian Council

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian minister of intelligence presented a report on Iran's security and intelligence situation during a meeting with President-elect Masoud Pezeshkian.
title: Minister of Intelligence holds meeting with Pezeshkian

description: TEHRAN – On Tuesday, Iran's acting Foreign Minister, Ali Baqeri Kani, delivered a speech at the United Nations Security Council, underscoring the incoming Iranian administration’s foreign policy focus on multilateralism.
title: Iran committed to multilateralism and international cooperation: acting FM

description: MADRID - In a column published this Saturday in the Tehran Times titled "My Message to the New World," Massoud Pezeshkian, the newly elected President of Iran, outlined his main points on foreign policy.
title: Continuity and change in Iran’s strategic culture

description: TEHRAN – Former U.S. President Donald Trump narrowly escaped an assassination attempt on Saturday during a rally in Pennsylvania, just days before he was expected to secure the Republican nomination for the third time.
title: Fishing in troubled waters

description: TEHRAN - The head of the Atomic Energy Organization of Iran has announced the launch of three new sites in the field of radiation at Iran's nuclear power plants.
title: Three new radiation sites established in Iran's nuclear plants: official

description: TEHRAN – Iran's acting Foreign Minister has commended Russia's efforts on the Palestinian issue during its presidency of the UN Security Council.
title: Tehran praises Moscow’s efforts towards Palestinian issue during UNSC presidency

description: TEHRAN - The chief of the planning office of the Hajj and Pilgrimage Organization has announced the start of registration of pilgrims participating in the Arbaeen Walk through the Samah system.
title: Registration process for Arbaeen Walk underway

description: TEHRAN – The Speaker of the Iranian Parliament has condemned the recent bombing of a school in the Nuseirat refugee camp in Gaza by Israeli forces, expressing confidence that Palestinians will ultimately reclaim their homeland.
title: Iranian Parliament speaker condemns Israeli bombing of Gaza school

description: TEHRAN – Local media reports from Saudi Arabia have indicated that Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman extended his congratulations to Iran's president-elect, Masoud Pezeshkian, via a phone call following his victory in the recent Iranian elections on Wednesday.
title: Iranian president-elect engages in phone conversations with world leaders

description: TEHRAN- Israel has ramped up deadly attacks across the Gaza Strip over the past days striking so-called “safe zones” where the Benjamin Netanyahu regime has ordered Palestinians to evacuate to for their safety.
title: Israel turns Gaza “safe zones” into massacre sites

description: TEHRAN- The Secretary-General of Lebanon’s Hezbollah, Seyyed Hassan Nasrallah, said on Tuesday that if the Israeli occupation regime “persists in targeting [Lebanese] civilians it would compel [Hezbollah] to launch rockets and target new settlements not previously targeted”.
title: Hezbollah chief warns Israeli occupation regime

description: Dr. Hassan Hamdan was one of the few trained plastic surgeons in Gaza, a specialist in wound reconstruction. His skills were vitally needed as Israel’s military onslaught filled hospitals with patients torn by blasts and shrapnel, so the 65-year-old came out of retirement to help, according to AP.
title: As Gaza’s doctors struggle to save lives, many lose their own in Israeli airstrikes

description: Protesters have gathered across the street from the Paris 2024 Olympic Games headquarters in Saint-Denis, just outside France’s capital, waving flags and banging pots and pans.
title: Calls for Paris 2024 to sanction Israel’s participation at Olympics

description: The US activist group Jewish Voice for Peace (JVP) has accused the Biden administration of "actively assisting" Israel in committing genocide in Gaza.
title: Jewish peace group: US actively assisting Israel’s genocide in Gaza

description: The Palestinian Red Crescent said its teams have treated 13 detainees including an elderly woman who was released by the Israeli army at the Kissufim checkpoint in central Gaza.
title: Palestinians released from detention recount torture, humiliation

description: The United Nations Children’s Fund has described the killing of three children by an Israeli air strike reportedly while they were playing in front of their home in south Lebanon, as “horrific”, in a post on social media.
title: UNICEF slams Israeli killing of children in Lebanon

description: Two drones attacked the Ayn al-Asad Airbase in Iraq's western Anbar province on Tuesday, where U.S. troops are stationed, an Iraqi army officer said.
title: Drones hit airbase housing U.S. forces in Iraq

description: TEHRAN - Ali Madawi, the chief of the Protocol Department at the Saudi Arabian Consulate in Mashhad, has paid a visit to the Great Museum of Khorasan.
title: Saudi diplomat visits Mashhad museum

description: TEHRAN - Zanjan province has welcomed tourists and photographers from nine countries to participate in the annual Tasu’a and Ashura mourning ceremonies, a significant religious event commemorating the martyrdom of Imam Hussain (AS).
title: Zanjan’s Muharram rituals attract foreign nationals

description: TEHRAN - Qazvin, renowned for its literary luminaries like Ubayd Zakani and Ali Akbar Dehkhoda, is launching a literary tourism department aimed at harnessing the rich cultural tapestry.
title: Qazvin literary heritage: a new frontier in tourism

description: TEHRAN - In a remarkable boost for local tourism, Golestan province recorded over eight million visits to its diverse attractions in the first quarter of the current Persian year (started on March 20), a local official brought to light.
title: 8 million visits to Golestan attractions registered

description: TEHRAN – Kermanshah’s cultural heritage department has commenced a systematic archaeological survey to determine the boundaries and propose a preservation area for a vast open-air Paleolithic site that is located in the western Iranian province.
title: Systematic archaeological survey begins at Paleolithic site in western Iran

description: TEHRAN – A habitat of migratory storks in Kordestan province has been officially registered on Iran’s national list of natural sites to help protect its serene atmosphere.
title: Stork habitat in Kordestan province gains national label

description: TEHRAN- An adaptation of Sophocles’ timeless tragedy “Antigone” is set to go on stage at Molavi Theater in Tehran in the near future.
title: “Antigone” to go on stage at Tehran theater

description: TEHRAN- The Cinematheque of the Iranian Artists Forum (IAF) will screen French filmmaker Quentin Dupieux’s 2023 black comedy movie “Yannick” on July 24.
title: IAF cinematheque to host “Yannick”

description: TEHRAN-Six short films from Iran will compete in the 13th RIURAU Film Festival, to be held in the Marina Alta region in Alicante (Spain) in August.
title: 6 Iranian short films to compete in Spain’s RIURAU Film Festival

description: TEHRAN – The number of international travelers observing religious rituals in Yazd during the first ten days of Muharram has doubled, according to a local official.
title: Muharram rituals in Yazd captivate intl. visitors

description: There is just a month until the beginning of the 2024 Paris Olympics, and athletes are getting their last allocation for the Olympics. The French security services have formed partnerships with 46 countries, trying to secure the safety of the matches. In addition to the French security protocols, Israel and the United States will send their own security forces to France in order to protect their athletes during the Games.
title: Presence of Israeli security forces contradicts the Spirit of the Olympics

description: TEHRAN- TEDPIX, the main index of the Tehran Stock Exchange (TSE), rose 1,545 points to 2,202,679 on Wednesday, which is the fifth day of the Iranian calendar week.
title: TEDPIX gains 1,500 points on Wednesday

description: TEHRAN – The Department of Environment (DOE) has increased penalties for wildlife crimes to deter offenses and strengthen conservation measures.
title: Penalties increased to curb wildlife crimes

description: TEHRAN – The Department of Environment (DOE) has registered five wetlands in Qom province in the list of national natural heritage sites.
title: Five wetlands in Qom on natural heritage sites list

description: TEHRAN –The vice president for women and family affairs has said that the administration of the late President Ebrahim Raisi adopted more than 20 new measures toward women’s development.
title: Over 20 new measures adopted for women’s development in Raisi administration

description: TEHRAN –Ali Salajeqeh, head of the Department of Environment (DOE), has announced the country’s readiness to provide Iraq with assistance to preserve the environment.
title: Tehran ready to aid Baghdad in preserving environment

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji says signing the agreement for transferring Russian gas to Iran is the masterpiece of the 13th administration's energy diplomacy which can pave the way for an economic revolution and ensure the region's energy security through Iran.
title: Oji praises Iran-Russia gas transfer agreement

description: TEHRAN – Over 33.97 billion cubic meters of water is stored behind the dams across Iran, indicating that 61 percent of the capacity of the country’s dams is full, according to the Iranian Energy Ministry data.
title: Water storage in Iranian dams rises 7%

description: TEHRAN - The Central Bank of Iran (CBI) has provided $20 billion in foreign currency for importing basic goods and commodities, medicines, and commercial goods since the beginning of the current Iranian calendar year (March 19, 2024) up to July 14, IRNA reported.
title: CBI provides over $20b in subsidized foreign currency for imports

description: TEHRAN - Iran's Ports and Maritime Organization (PMO) and the National Investments Agency of Kyrgyzstan approved a memorandum of understanding (MOU) for the development of the southern ports of Iran.
title: Iran, Kyrgyzstan approve MOU for port development

description: TEHRAN - The latest figures by the Statistical Center of Iran (SCI) puts the country’s jobless rate at 7.7 percent in the first three months of the current calendar year to late June.
title: Iran’s unemployment rate declines 0.5%

description: TEHRAN - A senior Iranian lawmaker has said the Islamic Republic is prepared to supply BRICS member states with oil and gas to meet their growing energy demands, IRNA reported.
title: ‘Iran ready to meet BRICS energy demands’

description: Cooperation for the development of high technologies and the exchange of knowledge and experience are among the leading topics in the interaction between the BRICS countries.
title: Archipelago 2024 discusses BRICS co-op in technology, climate
